        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/roessleville_new_york"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Roessle’s 11‑room Gothic Revival mansion on Central Avenue once had a stone‑lion gate that became today’s Elmhurst Avenue.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1,
        27,
        28
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
