        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roessleville%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Before farming, Roessleville lay within the Albany Pine Bush, a sandy pine barrens ecosystem that shaped early settlement.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4,
        6,
        30
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia",
        "Web source 1",
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roessleville%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Early farmers cleared the pine barrens with slash‑and‑burn, liming acidic soils and draining wetlands to grow hardy crops.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        29
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/roessleville_new_york"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Josiah and Elizabeth Stanford, parents of California Governor Leland Stanford, owned Elm Grove Farm here in 1840, boosting the hamlet’s growth.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
